33Address ConservativeStackVisitor::FindBasePtr(Address maybe_inner_ptr) const {
34 // Check if the pointer is contained by a normal or large page owned by this
35 // heap. Bail out if it is not.
36 const MemoryChunk* chunk =
37 allocator_->LookupChunkContainingAddress(maybe_inner_ptr);
38 if (chunk == nullptr) return kNullAddress;
39 const MemoryChunkMetadata* chunk_metadata = chunk->Metadata();
40 DCHECK(chunk_metadata->Contains(maybe_inner_ptr));
41 // If it is contained in a large page, we want to mark the only object on it.
42 if (chunk->IsLargePage()) {
43 // This could be simplified if we could guarantee that there are no free
44 // space or filler objects in large pages. A few cctests violate this now.
45 Tagged<HeapObject> obj(
46 static_cast<const LargePageMetadata*>(chunk_metadata)->GetObject());
47 PtrComprCageBase cage_base{chunk_metadata->heap()->isolate()};
48 return IsFreeSpaceOrFiller(obj, cage_base) ? kNullAddress : obj.address();
49 }
50 // Otherwise, we have a pointer inside a normal page.
51 const PageMetadata* page = static_cast<const PageMetadata*>(chunk_metadata);
52 // If it is not in the young generation and we're only interested in young
53 // generation pointers, we must ignore it.
54 if (Heap::IsYoungGenerationCollector(collector_) &&
55 !chunk->InYoungGeneration())
56 return kNullAddress;
57 // If it is in the young generation "from" semispace, it is not used and we
58 // must ignore it, as its markbits may not be clean.
59 if (chunk->IsFromPage()) return kNullAddress;
60 // Try to find the address of a previous valid object on this page.
61 Address base_ptr =
62 MarkingBitmap::FindPreviousValidObject(page, maybe_inner_ptr);
63 // Iterate through the objects in the page forwards, until we find the object
64 // containing maybe_inner_ptr.
65 DCHECK_LE(base_ptr, maybe_inner_ptr);
66 PtrComprCageBase cage_base{page->heap()->isolate()};
67 while (true) {
68 Tagged<HeapObject> obj(HeapObject::FromAddress(base_ptr));
69 const int size = obj->Size(cage_base);
70 DCHECK_LT(0, size);
71 if (maybe_inner_ptr < base_ptr + size)
72 return IsFreeSpaceOrFiller(obj, cage_base) ? kNullAddress : base_ptr;
73 base_ptr += size;
74 DCHECK_LT(base_ptr, page->area_end());
75 }
76}

78void ConservativeStackVisitor::VisitPointer(const void* pointer) {
79 auto address = reinterpret_cast<Address>(const_cast<void*>(pointer));
80 VisitConservativelyIfPointer<false>(address);
81#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
82 V8HeapCompressionScheme::ProcessIntermediatePointers(
83 cage_base_, address,
84 [this](Address ptr) { VisitConservativelyIfPointer<true>(ptr); });
85#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
86}
87
88template <bool is_known_to_be_in_cage>
89void ConservativeStackVisitor::VisitConservativelyIfPointer(Address address) {
90#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
91 if constexpr (!is_known_to_be_in_cage) {
92 // Bail out immediately if the pointer is not in the cage.
93 if (V8HeapCompressionScheme::GetPtrComprCageBaseAddress(address) !=
94 cage_base_.address())
95 return;
96 }
97 DCHECK_EQ(V8HeapCompressionScheme::GetPtrComprCageBaseAddress(address),
98 cage_base_.address());
99#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
100 // Bail out immediately if the pointer is not in the space managed by the
101 // allocator.
102 if (allocator_->IsOutsideAllocatedSpace(address)) {
103 DCHECK_EQ(nullptr, allocator_->LookupChunkContainingAddress(address));
104 return;
105 }
106 // Proceed with inner-pointer resolution.
107 Address base_ptr = FindBasePtr(address);
108 if (base_ptr == kNullAddress) return;
109 Tagged<HeapObject> obj = HeapObject::FromAddress(base_ptr);
110 Tagged<Object> root = obj;
111 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(delegate_);
112 delegate_->VisitRootPointer(Root::kStackRoots, nullptr,
113 FullObjectSlot(&root));
114 // Check that the delegate visitor did not modify the root slot.
115 DCHECK_EQ(root, obj);
116}
